key_concepts.explanation:
Common patterns that solve most loop problems:

ACCUMULATOR: Build up a total. int sum=0; for(...) sum += value;
COUNTER: Count occurrences. int count=0; for(...) if(match) count++;
SENTINEL: Loop until special value. while(input != -1) { process; input = next; }
SEARCH: Find first match. for(...) if(found) { result=item; break; }
MAX/MIN: Track best. int max=arr[0]; for(...) if(arr[i]>max) max=arr[i];
VALIDATION: Repeat until valid. do { ask; } while(!valid);

Recognising the pattern tells you which loop and which variables you need.

Practice tip: The best way to master loops is to TRACE them on paper. Write each iteration: what is the variable? Is the condition true? What does the body do? This builds deep understanding faster than just reading code.

